Package: pamlj
Type: Package
Title: Power Analysis for linear models 
Version: 0.2.2
Author: Marcello Gallucci
Maintainer: Marcello Gallucci <mcfanda@gmail.com>
Description:  A suite for power analysis for linear models.
             At the moment, it allows for power analysis of Pearson correlation
             and the general linear model (Anova/Regression/ANCOVA). The latter can be
             based on standardized coefficients (regression) or proportion of partial variance 
             effect siz (Eta-squared, Omega-Squared, Epsilon-Squared). It provides estimation
             of required sample size, power and minimally-detectable effect size, plus 
             plots for sensitivity analysis.
License: GPL-2
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: jmvcore (>= 0.8.0), pwr,viridis,rlang
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
